# Infrastructure and Reliability Perspective

From an engineering perspective, several recurring reliability risks appear:

| System Layer | Potential Failure Mode |
|---|---|
| Screening | missed identification or intake inconsistency |
| Coordination | fragmented communication across providers |
| Staff adoption | inconsistent intervention execution |
| Technical support | unresolved implementation drift |
| Post-release transition | loss of continuity of care |

The interviews imply that operational resilience depends heavily on redundancy, supervision, communication quality, and continuous monitoring processes.

