The evidence suggests several high-priority implementation improvements:

1. Standardized coordination protocols across organizations
2. Structured staff onboarding and supervision pipelines
3. Continuous implementation monitoring systems
4. Defined escalation and technical assistance workflows
5. Stronger transition infrastructure between jail and community care settings
6. Better operational support for transportation and follow-up coordination

